To read data from an Excel spreadsheet using Python, you can use the `pandas` library. Here's an example function:

```python
import pandas as pd

def read_excel(file_path):
    # Read the Excel file into a DataFrame
    df = pd.read_excel(file_path)

    return df
```

You can call this function by passing the path to your Excel file as an argument:

```python
data = read_excel('path/to/your/excel/file.xlsx')
print(data)  # Display the contents of the DataFrame
```
This will create a `pandas.DataFrame` object that you can manipulate and use for further analysis or processing.
